no use However the locals held\nthe Volunteers down to goose eggs\nthe last three Innings and the game\nresulted 3 to 2 In favor of Clarks\nvlllc\nvlllcPaducah\nPaducah succeeded In getting nine\nerror two being made the first\npop Latlncr was first up for the\nvisitors and Hew out to Cooper Mo\nCance followed going out Tidwcll to\nCooper Salnwater slapped one to\nMercer on short but the little player\nthrew wild and Rainwater succeed\ned in copping second bag Shlnii\nlanded one to short and on Coopers\nerror got to first Before Cooper\ncould regain the ball Rainwater\nscored Shinn was caught stealing\nsecond In the second Thompson\nfor the visitors swatted a twobag\nger Ho advanced to third when\nMcWllllams was being put out at\nfirst Payno stopped another score\nfor Clarksville by downing Blue at\nfirst Lockharts error in tho third\nresulted In Latlncr going to third\nwhen bo should have only gotten to\nfirst McCanco walked and while\ncaught stealing second Latlncr\ncrossed the skillet making two runs\nfor the visitors\nThe fourth ana fifth innings\npassed with neither side scoring\nand were featured by good team\nwork In the sixth Thompson sin\ngled and was followed on first bag\nby McWIllIanis when Manager\nCooper juggled the ball Thompson\nadvanced to second A clean hit by\nDlue over second base allowed\nThompson to score Hoyt went out\nsecond to first and McUllltams died\non second It was Paducahs time\ndo something nndvfor a while it\nlooked like the locals would come\nout victorious Mercer got to first\non an error of the second baseman\nAngcmolrcr drovo one past second\nand Mercer took the second bag\nPayno was put out at first while\nMercer took third with Angy on\nsecond Mercer scored while Lock\nhart went out at first Manager\nCooper won cheers by a hot one al\nlowing Angy to score Block flew\nout to center fielder\nA pretty catch by Block In right\nfield in the first of tho eighth pre\nvented Clarksvlllo from more scores\nThere were three men on tho bas